Pa še hude težave ima pri incompressible workloadu, ker pri tem gre kontroler v corner case in zgubi vsaj 1/3 write hitrosti.  Pa še to; intel je hudo razočaral, ko je enkrat prišlo na dan, da ne uporabljajo svojga firmwarea, ampak le modificirano varjanto referenčenga (tko kot vsi ostali).  SandForce's TRIM has never been fully functional when the drive is pushed into a corner with incompressible writes and the SSD 530 doesn't bring any change to that. This is really a big problem with SandForce drives if you're going to store lots of incompressible data (such as MP3s, H.264 videos and other highly compressed formats) because sequential speeds may suffer even more in the long run. As an OS drive the SSD 530 will do just fine since it won't be full of incompressible data, but I would recommend buying something non-SandForce if the main use will be storage of incompressible data.
